**Conventions:** "the file/plan" = current working file. "list of issues" = issues from last `review`/`fix-silent` pass, in report order; `fiximportant` takes topmost remaining. `timeout_sleep_ints` = no-op for files without timeout/sleep vars. "Clean" (`cleanstop`) = no content-changing edits in last pass.

**Naming:** Workers тАФ hyphen-case, exhaustive single-pass. Families тАФ snake_case, wrap a worker in `timeout_sleep_ints`/`cleanstop`, accept `max=N`. Loop functions тАФ hyphen-case, process the issue list one item at a time, built-in cap.

**Pipeline family pattern** (`max=1` default; invoke `<family> max=N`): (1) `timeout_sleep_ints` (2) worker (3) final step (4) if `max>1`: `cleanstop`, else repeat from step 2 up to `maxтИТ1` more times.

| Family | Worker | Final | Cap |
|---|---|---|---|
| `fix` | `fix-silent` | `linesme` | 5 |
| `broad` | `fix-broad-silent` | `linesme` | 5 |
| `security` | `fix-security-silent` | `linesme` | 5 |
| `perf_review` | `fix-perf-review-silent` | `showme` | 4 |
| `api_review` | `fix-api-review-silent` | `showme` | 4 |
| `md_update` | `md-update-silent` | `showme` | 4 |
| `schema` | `schema-update-silent` | `showme` | 4 |

`sequential-fixes` is a loop (not a family): `fiximportant; cleanstop, else fiximportant again` ├Ч10 max.

**One true file (always):** copy any file to a single working path immediately; all edits go there; `cp` workingтЖТoutputs only when presenting; never edit the presented copy; view the working path immediately before every `str_replace`.

**Describe:** `describe-behavior` тАФ one-sentence job, capability bullets with specific numbers, CLI flags, line count + deps; don't trust the docstring. `describe-structure` тАФ entry point, call hierarchy, state machines, exception flow, external interfaces; flag docstring divergence; group workarounds by root cause. `describe-structure-deep` тАФ same but exhaustive: every workaround, its forcing constraint, shared-root siblings, and the clean design.

**Plan:** `plan-review-api` тАФ API-expert review (surface area, naming, defaults, error contracts); no edits. `plan-simplify-silent` тАФ cut overspecified/redundant/speculative/duplicate; collapse, generalize, drop; iterate until further cuts lose load-bearing content; no commentary. `simplify-plan` тАФ `plan-simplify-silent` + report line count and what was cut. `simplify-plan-deeper` тАФ `simplify-plan` ├Ч3 max if cuts were made. `plan-score` тАФ score 5 categories ├Ч sub-metrics (1тАУ5): API quality, implementation clarity, test coverage, risk management, doc quality; identify highest-leverage changes; comparison table if a prior version exists.

**Filesystem:** `showskillfs` тАФ ls /mnt/skills/{public,examples,user}/. `showtranscriptfs` тАФ ls /mnt/transcripts/. `showprojectfs` тАФ ls /mnt/project. `showuserfs` тАФ ls /home/claude/, outputs/, uploads/, tool_results. `showmyfs` тАФ showuserfs + showskillfs + showtranscriptfs + showprojectfs. `mtime_output` тАФ outputs/ files with MDT mtimes. `mtime_claude` тАФ same for /home/claude/. `touch_start` тАФ touch /home/claude/tmp_session_start; mtime_output (optional explicit marker). `session_time` тАФ CURRENT-CONTAINER reading (resets on restart by design; use chat_time for wall-clock): start = max(container boot `awk '/^btime/{print $2}' /proc/stat`, mtime tmp_session_start if present) `start=$((s>=b?s:b))`; diff to now тЖТ "Session time: Xm Ys"; btime floor means a stale/absent marker can't skew it. `touch_chat_start` тАФ touch outputs/tmp_chat_start; mtime_output (optional; no longer the primary chat anchor). `chat_time` тАФ WALL-CLOCK since chat opened (survives restarts): anchor `co` = earliest immutable mtime in /mnt/user-data/uploads/ (тЙИ chat open), else tmp_session_start, else btime; use `co` directly (NO btime floor) тЖТ "Chat time: Xh Ym Ys". `session_time_header` тАФ silently at start of every response: first append btime to /home/claude/.boot_history (dedup `grep -qx`) so show_time.sh's reboot counter catches every restart, then print CURRENT-CONTAINER "тП▒ Session: Xm Ys" (start=max(btime,tmp_session_start)); /proc/stat always exists so it no longer skips when the marker is missing.

`showhotfs` тАФ list hot files (CREATED/MODIFIED/DELETED this chat) vs COLD originals; report only. Three areas: (A) /home/claude/ + outputs/ тАФ md5 each non-dot file (dedup same-name across the two), classify vs uploads/ + /mnt/project: CREATED (no same-named original) / MODIFIED (show origin md5) / COLD-COPY (=an original тЖТ not hot, list apart). (B) /mnt/project/ тАФ diff vs the CHAT-START baseline = the export zip that populated it, found by `unzip-project`'s rule but scanning uploads/ ONLY (never outputs/): `meehan_project_export_*_v<N>.zip`, most recent date, highest `_v<N>` tiebreaker (uploads-only is why a zip built into outputs/ this chat isn't picked); map each zip entry to its post-flatten relpath (strip wrapper + `tierN_` dir; tier1 + tier2 root files тЖТ project root, tier2 `scripts/`//`narrative/` + all tier3 keep subpaths), md5 тЖТ snapshot; per current file by relpath: CREATED (absent in baseline) / MODIFIED (show baseline md5) / skip-unchanged; DELETED = baseline relpaths now absent (show old md5). Fallback (no import zip in uploads/): cutoff = WALL-CLOCK chat-open anchor `co` (earliest immutable uploads/ mtime тЙИ chat open, survives restarts; else tmp_session_start; else container boot as deepest last resort) тАФ NOT btime, because an edit made before a mid-chat restart has mtime < btime and a btime cutoff would miss it; `co` predates the restart and catches it. mtimeтЙе`co` = touched-this-chat only (can't subclassify CREATED/MODIFIED or detect DELETED without the zip baseline; flatten touches everything тАФ coarse last resort). not-state (excluded everywhere): `*.zip`/`*.xpi`/`claude-debug-extension/`/`web-ext-artifacts/`/build dirs + `_paste*.json`/`tmp_session_start`/`tmp_chat_start`/`.session_counts`/`.reconcile_state.json`/`.git/`/`__pycache__/`. Per-area tables: file|loc|status|bytes|md5 (+origin/baseline md5 for MODIFIED, old md5 for DELETED).

**Output modifiers:** `dont_narrate_fixes` тАФ no fix narration. `skip_post-round_summary` тАФ no summary. `no_fix_list` тАФ no fix list before files. `showme` тАФ present modified output files with MDT mtimes. `showmeall` тАФ present all output files with MDT mtimes. `jump-to-bottom` тАФ jump to bottom. `cleanstop` тАФ if clean stop, else showme; jump-to-bottom.

**Single-shot:** `review` тАФ report all issues, no fixes. `linesme` тАФ line count. `timeout_sleep_ints` тАФ verify timeout/sleep vars are integers; no-op otherwise. `fiximportant` тАФ fix topmost remaining issue. `sequential-fixes` тАФ loop (above). `rewrite` тАФ (1) timeout_sleep_ints (2) fix-rewrite-keepcomments-silent (3) linesme. `otf` тАФ confirm one-true-file active. `do_acid` тАФ activate ACID from `claude_acid_2.md`; if absent locally, fetch from `https://raw.githubusercontent.com/levitation29/claude/refs/heads/main/claude_acid_2.md` silently and save to `/home/claude/claude_acid_2.md`; snapshot all /home/claude/ files lacking one, register default invariants, confirm; if already active re-snapshot and re-confirm; follow SNAPSHOT/EDIT/PUBLISH/RESTORE.

**Workers:** `fix-silent` тАФ fix all bugs silently. `fix-broad-silent` тАФ fix-silent + style/naming/comments/dead code. `fix-security-silent` тАФ fix injection/privilege/leakage/unsafe silently. `fix-perf-review-silent` тАФ perf-expert review, flag issues, then sequential-fixes. `fix-api-review-silent` тАФ API-expert review, flag issues, then sequential-fixes. `md-update-silent` тАФ update .md with impl details (esp. error handling), then sequential-fixes. `schema-update-silent` тАФ update .schema with full SQL behavior range, then sequential-fixes. `fix-rewrite-silent` тАФ rewrite unclean sections, no commentary. `fix-rewrite-keepcomments-silent` тАФ same, keep all comments.

**Counters:** `session_counts` тАФ read/increment turn count in /home/claude/.session_counts (`turns tools`), write back, print "ЁЯФв Turn N ┬╖ tool calls so far: C". `session_counts_header` тАФ silently run session_counts at start of every response, print result first; skip if unwritable. `session_counts_resync T C` тАФ write "T C" to .session_counts directly; both args required. `trim_for_preferences` тАФ read `command_2.notes` (uploads or working path); produce a condensed paste-ready version (strip prose/motivation/examples/cross-session blocks; bold inline section labels; one terse line per command); save `command_2_preferences.notes`, publish to outputs. `xyzzy` тАФ touch_start; session_time_header; session_counts; session_counts_header. Tool call must be literally the first thing in the response, no text before it.

**HUD audit (claude_browser_extension.sh):** `hud_audit` тАФ paste a `_claudeDebug.audit()` snapshot; persist to /home/claude/hud_ledger.json (create + announce if missing; else append as next `entry`, bump `next_entry`); after each write `cp` тЖТ outputs/hud_ledger.json; treat that file as authoritative history тАФ flatten all `entries[].snapshot.data`, dedup rows by `id`, assess the new paste vs all stored history (TTFT, total time, tok/s, output size, thinking-vs-answer share, stop reasons, error/limit signals); also append an in-conversation numbered entry mirroring the file `entry`; flag drift and outliers; correlations not proof; at session start, if ledger absent rebuild from any uploaded hud_ledger.json, else start fresh at entry 1.

**Session resume:** Projects don't accept/auto-extract `.zip` тАФ persist files INDIVIDUALLY in the Project's Files section (they appear at /mnt/project/<name> next chat); a `.zip` is usable only attached to a chat (тЖТ /mnt/user-data/uploads/, unzip there). md5 = change-detection. `resume_seed` тАФ write `resume_seed.md` (one-true path, publish to outputs); facts only from real files/this session, never invent; five literal-heading sections `resume` parses тАФ **RESUME** (one line: resuming; session start = touch_start + counters; follow command system; for any command not in live prefs use attached `command_2_preferences.notes`); **MANIFEST** (table, one row per state file: `working_name | store_as | role | required|optional | origin(project|upload|session) | modified(y/n) | bytes | lines | md5`; add stale /mnt/project md5 when origin=project & modified=y; exclude regenerable `.zip`/`.xpi`; `store_as` renames odd extensions to .md/.txt/.json); **LEDGER** (if `hud_ledger.json` is state: entries, unique rows by id, id list, next entry); **STATE** (done edits; OPEN items; DONE one-offs); **START** (run `resume`). `resume` тАФ run FIRST in a new chat: (1) `touch_start` + counters; (2) read MANIFEST/LEDGER/STATE/START from pasted seed or uploaded `resume_seed.md`; (3) locate each file: /mnt/project/<store_as>, then /mnt/user-data/uploads/ (incl. extracting an uploaded `.zip`), then working paths тАФ never seek a `.zip` in /mnt/project; (4) md5sum + compare тЖТ тЬУmatch / тЪаmismatch ("equals known-stale" when so) / тЬЧabsent; (5) on any required тЪа/тЬЧ STOP + print upload checklist (filename + why), never accept md5тЙаmanifest, no proceed unless user says "proceed degraded"; (6) confirm тЬУ/тЬЧ table and await next command тАФ NEVER cp any file to a working path during resume; user sets up one-true-file when starting work; blind cp could overwrite a fresher upload.

**zip-project** тАФ OUTPUT side: run `resume_seed` first, then `make_export.sh` (per create_zip_by_tiers.md ┬з7) тЖТ classifies via `export_rules.conf` using `check_export_rules.sh` (flags UNMATCHED/AMBIGUOUS), stages tiers atomically, gates (no UNMATCHED, non-empty tier1, zip_version==N), refuses NтЙдlast, writes README w/ archiveHash+sessionNonce, emits `meehan_project_export_<DATE>_v<N>.zip` to outputs/; `make_export.sh --dry-run` to preview, `check_export_rules.sh <roots>` to validate. Producing the zip doesn't persist тАФ human downloads + re-uploads via UI. Edits are LIVE on /mnt/project (update_tree.py atomic, nonce-stamped); no staging/promote step.

**unzip-project** тАФ (1) Scan /mnt/user-data/uploads/ for `*_YYYY-MM-DD_v<N>.zip`; select most recent by date, highest `_v<N>` as tiebreaker. (2) If /mnt/project/ is non-empty: warn and ask тАФ wipe (delete all first) or overwrite (same paths only)? If overwrite: list all paths inside the zip; if any file's relative path differs only in top-level folder from an existing file in /mnt/project/ with the same basename тЖТ abort with conflict report. (3) Confirm: "Unzip `<file>` to /mnt/project/ [wipe first / overwrite]?" тАФ await y/n. (4) On y: wipe if chosen (`rm -rf /mnt/project/*`), then `unzip -o <path> -d /mnt/project/`. (5) If tiers landed under a single top-level wrapper dir (usual тАФ the export carries its own folder, so /mnt/project/<wrapper>/tier1_live_state/... not /mnt/project/tier1_live_state/...): note `resume` expects files flat at /mnt/project/<store_as> and RUN `flatten.sh here --yes` (the unified flattener; tier-merges into /mnt/project/: tier1 contents + tier2 WHOLE-DIR (root .md specs тЖТ root, scripts/ & narrative/ as subdirs) + tier3 contents; overwrite-same-name, never delete; prompts before removing the wrapper; ends with showmyfs); runs automatically as the final import step (unzip-project = unzip + flatten). (6) `showmyfs`.
